    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-13T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-13T14:00:00-05:00" n="270"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50A/75: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Counselor of Legation in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Geneva</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-13T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 13, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>131. Your 223, January 12, 2 p.m.<note n="30" xml:id="d270fn30">Not
                        printed.</note> If you receive notification of meeting of Committee for
                    technical cooperation between the League and China, with invitation to attend,
                    Department desires that you give an informal acceptance and attend in an
                    absolutely informal and strictly unofficial capacity. Department is instructing
                    Paris to send you text or substance of instructions issued to Marriner<note
                        n="32" xml:id="d270fn32">J. Theodore Marriner, Counselor of Embassy in
                        France.</note> in connection with his attendance in July, 1933, at meeting
                    of this Committee.<note n="33" xml:id="d270fn33">See telegram No. 145, July 16,
                        1933, midnight, from the Acting Secretary of State to the Secretary of State
                        in London, <ref target="frus1933v03#pg_499">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1933, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 499</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
